Today myself, my 2yr old daughter and her grandparents stop by to try the spot we been trying to visit since it open and we was definitely not disappointed. We had such an amazing visit from the gentleman who held the door, the superrrrr helpful guy (I wish I wouldn’t catch his name) at the counter assisting us on how to place our larger order as we were trying to figure out and accommodate everyone in our party, to the staff  coming and checking on us throughout our entire visit. Everyone was so friendly and the place was clean and sanitizer was available. In the middle of our visit, my Mother-In-Law accidentally locked the keys in the car and mention it to a staff member (Mike) and with no hesitation he offer to go and check it and see if he could assist. He did in fact get the door open so we could retrieve the keys. We really appreciate Mike for going out his way to help! If y’all haven’t already you really got to go and check out Dee’s Xquisite, wait times wasn’t long, food was hot and fresh with that spicy kick oh and that butter garlic sauce was BOMB!
